<paragraph id="D20C3697FFD8FFF4A1987EBC91E10CE5" blockId="17.[145,761,1509,1684]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD8FFF4A1987EBC914B0F8A" box="[145,299,1510,1531]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Medium or large adult-sized 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD8FFF4A1987D5E91040C6B" authorityName="BERRY" authorityYear="1912" box="[145,356,1540,1562]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1229" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Octopoteuthoidea">Octopoteuthoidea</taxonomicName>
with two series of hooks on most arms; with photophores at the tips of one or more pairs of arms; with large, broad, muscular fins, fin length almost the same as the mantle length, fused together along dorsal midline.
</paragraph>
